# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the values are
#   specific to the developer's environment, but other developers might want to share them.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different python versions passed,
#   Pipfile.lock might be ocularly different. In most cases, ignore is not recommended.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock is database of dependencies and should be checked in.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock is database of dependencies and should be checked in.
# pdm.lock

